             type="script"
             releaseDate="20241126">
      <title>
        Nebular Ionization Structure Analyzer
      </title>
      <description>
        <p>
          A comprehensive PixInsight script for analyzing narrowband astronomical images (Hα, OIII, SII).
          The script generates line ratio maps, pixel classification (shock-dominated, high-ionization, photoionized regions),
          ionization front detection using multiscale analysis, and CSV reports with statistical metrics.
        </p>
        <p>
          Features:
        </p>
        <p>
          • Automatic ratio map computation (SII/Hα, OIII/Hα, OIII/SII)
        </p>
        <p>
          • Pixel classification based on configurable thresholds
        </p>
        <p>
          • Multiscale ionization front detection
        </p>
        <p>
          • CSV report generation with area, mean ratio, and max ratio statistics
        </p>
        <p>
          • PNG overlay visualization
        </p>
        <p>
          Requirements: Input channels must be calibrated, aligned, and background-subtracted (DBE) before processing.
        </p>
      </description>
    </package>
  </platform>
</xri>

